Why Linear Models?
Linear models are simple, easy to interpret, and often provide a good baseline for many machine learning problems. They work well when there is a linear relationship between the features and the target. However, when relationships in the data are more complex (non-linear), more advanced models like decision trees, neural networks, or ensemble methods might be needed.